OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1773684358
OL,3,CElusive nightjar's 'remarkable
OL,4,Ccomeback' to South Downs National Park
OL,6,FThe nightjar is listed as an amber
OL,7,Fspecies under the Red List for Birds,
OL,8,Fmeaning it is a species of
OL,9,F"conservation concern" with their
OL,10,Fnumbers falling by 51% between 1972
OL,11,Fand 1992 following loss of woodland
OL,12,Fand heathland to agriculture and
OL,13,Fdevelopment.
OL,15,FNightjars are crepuscular birds
OL,16,Fmeaning they emerge at twilight and
OL,17,Fcan be seen hunting for food at dusk
OL,18,Fand dawn.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@VO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1773684358
OL,3,CElusive nightjar's 'remarkable
OL,4,Ccomeback' to South Downs National Park
OL,6,FThe birds migrate 4,000 miles from the
OL,7,FDemocratic Republic of Congo each
OL,8,Fspring and remain from April to August.
OL,10,FThe national park spokesman said: "The
OL,11,Fbird is known by many names ` the fern
OL,12,Fowl, the wheeler, the nightchurr and
OL,13,Fthe dor-hawk but the oddest is the
OL,14,Fgoatsucker.
OL,16,F"Long ago it was thought nightjars
OL,17,Fwould drink milk directly from goats,
OL,18,Fpoisoning them so their udders wasted
OL,19,Faway and they went blind.
OL,26,@rD@cOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1773684358
OL,3,CElusive nightjar's 'remarkable
OL,4,Ccomeback' to South Downs National Park
OL,6,F"The myth was once common in many
OL,7,Fcountries all over Europe.
OL,9,F"The legend probably arose from the
OL,10,Ffact that nightjars were coming close
OL,11,Fto livestock because they were hunting
OL,12,Finsects nearby."
OL,14,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,15,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,16,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,17,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,18,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,19,Fbelow...
